The '''Swadeshi Jagaran Manch''' is a political and cultural organisation founded in 1991. It promotes national self reliance. Its background is in the [[Swadeshi movement]] that was part of the [[Indian independence movement]]. It is an affiliate of the [[Hindutva|Hindu nationalist]] [[Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh]] that deals with economic issues.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Thacker|first1=Teena|title=RSS arm raises questions over govt’s draft policy on pharma|url=http://www.livemint.com/Politics/Xov74Swggc6CMWnifK4mdK/RSS-arm-raises-questions-over-govts-draft-policy-on-pharma.html|website=Live Mint|accessdate=8 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=SJM wants fresh cooked food to fight malnutrition in kids|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sjm-wants-fresh-cooked-food-to-fight-malnutrition-in-kids/1/1032623.html|accessdate=8 September 2017|work=India Today|date=August 23, 2017}}</ref> [[Swaminathan Gurumurthy]] is a co-convener of the organisation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/bhatt-vs-gujarat-govt-hacked-email-vs-email/827972/0|title=Bhatt vs Gujarat govt: Hacked email vs email|accessdate=2011-08-08}}</ref>
==Political positions== Since at least 2015 the SJM has been critical of [[foreign direct investment]].<ref>http://www.firstpost.com/business/rss-affiliated-swadeshi-jagaran-manch-opposes-fdi-in-single-brand-retail-foreign-investment-in-air-india-4298843.html</ref><ref>https://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/we-want-a-white-paper-on-costs-and-benefits-of-fdi/293538</ref>
